        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">The provided European production volume is an estimated value as described below. 
According to 'Ullmann's encyclopaedia of industrial chemistry', version published in 2011, the United States production volume of cyclohexane in 2000 was approximated to 1'500'000'000 kg and amounted to 34% of the world production.
In 2019, the United States production volume amounted to 860'000'000 kg, based on: &lt;https://www.statista.com/statistics/974749/us-cyclohexane-production-volume/&gt;, last accessed 25-09-2023.
Hence, the global cyclohexane production volume was estimated based on the 2019s USA production and the respective world share from 2000.
The European counterpart is estimated to be 110'504'024 kg, considering the nominal GDP of EU in 2000, equal to 6'495'755'148'669 US$ and in the World, equal to                                     33'845'583'188'360 US$, available here: &lt;https://api.worldbank.org/v2/en/indicator/NY.GDP.MKTP.CD?downloadformat=excel&gt; , last accessed 23-09.2023.
References:
Cave, M., Falkner, K. C., &amp; McClain, C. (2012). Chapter 27 - Occupational and Environmental Hepatotoxicity. In T. D. Boyer, M. P. Manns, &amp; A. J. Sanyal (Eds.), Zakim and Boyer’s Hepatology (Sixth Edition) (pp. 476-492). W.B. Saunders. &lt;https://doi.org/https://doi.org/10.1016/B978-1-4377-0881-3.00027-9&gt;


</productionVolumeComment>
